PROJECT TITLE: GCC Code Analyzer (Function & Variable Extractor)

DESCRIPTION:
This project is developed using Python. The main purpose of this program is to analyze a C source file and extract useful information from it.
## re - Regular Expressions Used for Pattern matching, Searching text, Extracting specific parts from strings.
## No Other package used in this code

It provides details such as:

* Function names along with their return types
* Function parameters
* Global variables with their datatypes
* Local variables with their datatypes
* Function calls (caller → callee relationship)
* Inline functions present in the code

FEATURES:

1. Removes comments from the given C code
2. Detects all functions in the program
3. Identifies both global and local variables
4. Shows the relationship between function calls
5. Detects inline functions (including static inline)
6. Supports common datatypes like int, float, double, char, long, short, unsigned, and bool

HOW TO RUN:

Step 1: Make sure Python is installed on your system

Step 2: Place your C file (for example: input.c) in the same folder as the program

Step 3: Run the program using the following command:
python c_code_anlyzer.py

Step 4: After running, the output will be displayed in the terminal

OUTPUT:
The program displays:

* Global variables
* Total number of global variables
* Function details, including:
  • Function name
  • Return type
  • Parameters
  • Local variables
  • Number of local variables
  • Function calls
* Inline functions present in the code

